<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-53-0356 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper reports on the symposium on civil nuclear power, which was partof the 'Clean Air Conference', Brighton, United Kingdom, 1987. The environmentalbenefits of nuclear power are described, as well as the need for nuclearpower, reactor safety, radioactive waste, and the public acceptabilityof nuclear power. Doses of radioactivity from natural and artificialsources are given, along with the annual dose from nuclear industry discharges,and doses from sources such as medical procedures. Radiation monitoringschemes introduced by local authorities, and the economics of power generationare also discussed.</TEXT></DOC>